import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

The chart title is set to "Is there a correlation between width and height in the dataset?". The `plot` function returns the `plt` object, which can be used to display or save the chart.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['width'] = pd.to_numeric(data['width'], errors='coerce')
    data['height'] = pd.to_numeric(data['height'], errors='coerce')
    avg_width = data['width'].mean()
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(['Width', 'Height'], [avg_width, avg_height], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e'])
    ax.axhline(avg_width, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Width: {avg_width:.2f}')
    ax.axhline(avg_height, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average width and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.astype({'width': 'float', 'height': 'float'})
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['width'], bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='Width')
    ax.hist(data['height'], bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='Height')
    ax.axvline(data['width'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Width: {:.2f}'.format(data['width'].mean()))
    ax.axvline(data['height'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Height: {:.2f}'.format(data['height'].mean()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of width and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
